    "# FINAL REPORT ON MACHINE LEARNING \n",
    "## Unsupervised Machine Learning for Clustering Firms by Creditworthiness Based on Financial Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0b142574-4f93-4f87-9eb8-3d3b219c7dea",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **1. Introduction**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ceb98197-dae6-40f5-826c-4fd1e1afba15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.1 Background and motivation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f04db865-f16d-4e6b-82e8-6a97ab58adc8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In recent years, the evaluation and classification of corporate creditworthiness have become increasingly important, especially in emerging markets such as Vietnam. With the rapid growth of the financial sector, the demand for data-driven methods to support risk management and decision-making has risen significantly. Traditional credit rating models are often rule-based or rely heavily on expert judgment, which can be subjective and time-consuming.\n",
    "\n",
    "Unsupervised machine learning, especially clustering techniques, offers an alternative by automatically discovering patterns in data without predefined labels. In this study, we explore how clustering algorithms can be applied to classify the creditworthiness of non-financial firms listed on the Vietnamese stock market, using financial statement data provided by FiinGroup for the period from 2021 to 2024.\n",
    "\n",
    "The motivation behind this research is to provide an objective and data-driven view of corporate credit risk, which can support financial institutions, investors, and policymakers in identifying groups of firms with similar risk profiles.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "81417567-1c9f-458b-a56a-c16c236837b2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.2 Research objectives"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e2ce92cb-efbf-4ee6-996e-57cf0f259e43",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This project aims to:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Apply unsupervised machine learning techniques to cluster Vietnamese non-financial firms based on their financial indicators.\n",
    "\n",
    "* Compare the clustering performance of KMeans and Gaussian Mixture Models (GMM).\n",
    "\n",
    "* Evaluate the interpretability and suitability of each method in the context of creditworthiness analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "* Propose the most appropriate model to classify firms by credit risk, supporting further credit analysis or portfolio management."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ac8e0db7-0cba-47db-a721-886e4f18bf51",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1.3 Research questions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f4d58d5-78f5-47ce-be2f-60824c44277f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The main research questions guiding this study are:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. How effectively can unsupervised clustering algorithms identify meaningful creditworthiness groups among non-financial firms in Vietnam?\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Between KMeans and Gaussian Mixture Models, which algorithm produces clusters that better reflect financial characteristics related to credit risk?\n",
    "\n",
    "3. What are the strengths and limitations of each model when applied to financial statement data in the Vietnamese context?"
   ]
  },
